From Ann Carlson Subject Re Homosexuality issues in Christianity In article M , Dan Schaertel,,, writes In article , Ann Carlson writes Anyone who thinks being gay and Christianity are not compatible should check out Dignity, Integrity, More Light Presbyterian churches, Affirmation, MCC churches, etc Meet some gay Christians, find out who they are, pray with them, discuss scripture with them, and only then form your opinion If you were to start your own religion, this would be fine But there is no scriptural basis for your statement, How about Acts , or, I John which says to try the spirits to see if they be of God in fact it really gets to the heart of the problem You think you know more than scripture Your faith is driven by feel goodism and not by the Word of God How do you know When have you tried to learn anything about me Dr Ann B Carlson O MS o NASA Langley Research Center Hampton, VA